<dl id="n12100j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12100j">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12100j"> 100(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> built in eclipse on / Good Friday</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Que le navire ait quelque d&eacute;fectuosit&eacute; dans sa construction ou paraisse vou&eacute; &agrave; la malchance, il ne tiendra pas bien la mer, il ne pourra pas se comporter comme il faudrait aux jours de gros temps. Et, si le <i>mauvais &oelig;il</i> s&apos;est attach&eacute; &agrave; lui, le poisson insensible &agrave; l&apos;app&acirc;t que lui jetteront les p&ecirc;cheurs, fuira les filets qu&apos;ils lui tendent, et quelque jour un coup de vent soudain ou une temp&ecirc;te le feront chavirer. Il importe qu&apos;il soit solidement construit. <br><font color="green">[When the boat has some defect in its construction or seems destined to have bad luck, it will not ride well on the sea, it will not behave as it should on days with bad weather. And if the &ldquo;evil eye&rdquo; is on it, the fish will be blind to the bait that the fishermen throw at them and will flee their nets, and one day a sudden wind or a tempest will make it capsize. It must be built solidly.]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="PYLB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#PYLB"><cite title="source">La Bretagne et ses Traditions</cite></a> (1898) 52</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
